\textit{\small TypeScript \textperiodcentered{} NestJS \textperiodcentered{} Node.js \textperiodcentered{} MongoDB \textperiodcentered{} RabbitMQ}
\begin{itemize}
  \item Delivered production-quality REST API handling multichannel payment processing with NestJS and TypeScript — event-driven async processing via RabbitMQ, full test coverage, zero regressions on deployment
  \item Applied clean architecture separating domain logic from infrastructure — independent testing of business rules and straightforward integration of new payment providers
\end{itemize}

\vspace{4pt}
\textbf{EstateFlow — Real estate platform}\\
\textit{\small TypeScript \textperiodcentered{} React \textperiodcentered{} Next.js \textperiodcentered{} NestJS \textperiodcentered{} PostgreSQL}
\begin{itemize}
  \item Built customer-facing dashboard for real estate agents — translating complex property data and market trends into simple, actionable insights that accelerated deal decisions
  \item Shipped full-stack platform with Next.js SSR and React component library using lean experimentation — prototyped core features rapidly, validated with real users, then productionized with NestJS backend and PostgreSQL with GDPR-compliant data handling
  \item Optimized for Core Web Vitals and mobile-first experience — sub-second response times on complex property filtering across large datasets
\end{itemize}

% ── EXPERIENCE ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
\section{Experience}

\textbf{Senior Backend Engineer — Mili Gold} \hfill \textit{Nov 2023 – Present}\\
\small Mili Gold is a gold-backed digital assets and payments platform with 20M daily active users.
\begin{itemize}
  \item Built an internal \textbf{NL-to-SQL analytics assistant} (Node.js · TypeScript · OpenAI · PostgreSQL) enabling Mili Gold's marketing team to self-serve campaign and user-engagement queries across \textbf{20M+ daily users} in plain English — analyst request turnaround from \textasciitilde{}2 days to seconds; per-query LLM cost reduced \textasciitilde{}60\% via RAG with column pruning, Redis semantic caching, and token-aware rate limiting; all generated queries validated read-only against a \textbf{PostgreSQL read replica} with results streamed over \textbf{WebSocket} to a lightweight React interface
  \item Eliminated daily blocking transactions for 20M users — rebuilt a broken 34-state machine into an 8-state model with Kafka exactly-once processing, idempotency keys, and retry-inquiry mechanism hardened against real production failure cases
  \item Reduced critical query execution from 4 minutes to under 1 second by restructuring indexes and rewriting inefficient query plans in PostgreSQL — zero degradation under peak load
  \item Improved deployment reliability to near-zero flaky failures by eliminating unstable integration tests — unblocked release cadence and enabled faster feature flag rollouts across the pipeline
  \item Owned end-to-end observability across financial workflows — alerting, tracing, and performance budgets integrated into CI/CD
\end{itemize}

\vspace{4pt}
\textbf{Backend Engineer — AbanTether} \hfill \textit{Feb 2022 – Nov 2023}\\
\small AbanTether is a crypto exchange platform processing high-frequency financial events for 1M+ users and 400K+ active wallets across 8 blockchain networks.
\begin{itemize}
  \item Served 1M+ users at thousands of requests per second with sub-10ms latency by building an event-driven microservice with async worker pools — replaced polling architecture with real-time data pipeline
  \item Eliminated \textasciitilde{}90\% of failed transaction interventions by redesigning async Kafka workflows with circuit breaker, retry, and DLQ patterns — self-healing system under transient failures
  \item Built robust data ingestion pipeline reconciling transaction states across 8 blockchain networks — ensured zero fund loss during network partitions and external provider timeouts
  \item Reduced infrastructure cost by \textasciitilde{}90\% through connection pooling, async processing, and query optimization across PostgreSQL and MongoDB
\end{itemize}

\vspace{4pt}
\textbf{Backend Engineer — NuraFinTech} \hfill \textit{Mar 2020 – Feb 2022}\\
\small Remote — Early-stage fintech infrastructure company building distributed payment processing systems.
\begin{itemize}
  \item Delivered zero-loss message guarantees across banking integrations by designing transactional outbox patterns — eliminated distributed transaction complexity entirely
  \item Built multi-currency settlement and reconciliation pipelines with full observability and state consistency across unreliable external systems
  \item Operated in a fast-moving early-stage environment — shipped reliable financial infrastructure incrementally, validating each integration before scaling
\end{itemize}

